I tried cfg nightly feature `const_trait_impl` and I get a compilation error with the following code:
```rust
#![cfg_attr(feature = "const_fn", feature(const_trait_impl))]

#[cfg(not(feature = "const_fn"))]
fn const_fn<T>(t: T) {}

#[cfg(feature = "const_fn")]
use std::marker::Destruct;

#[cfg(feature = "const_fn")]
const fn const_fn<T>(t: T)
where
    T: ~const Destruct,
{
}

fn main() {
    const_fn(12);
}
```
But this leads to compile error (with `cargo run`):
```
error[E0658]: const trait impls are experimental                                                 
  --> src\main.rs:12:8                                                                           
   |                                                                                             
13 |     T: ~const Destruct,                                                                     
   |        ^^^^^^                                                                               
   |                                                                                             
   = note: see issue #67792 <https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/67792> for more information
   = help: add `#![feature(const_trait_impl)]` to the crate attributes to enable                 
                                                                                                 
For more information about this error, try `rustc --explain E0658`.
```

For example, with `try_blocks` feature there is no compile error:
```rust
#![cfg_attr(feature = "try_fn", feature(try_blocks))]

#[cfg(feature = "try_fn")]
fn try_fn() {
    let x: Option<_> = try { 123 };
}

#[cfg(not(feature = "try_fn"))]
fn try_fn() {}

pub fn main() {
    try_fn();
}
```
I think it looks like a bug, is it?
---
I use `nightly-x86_64-pc-windows-msvc - rustc 1.64.0-nightly (93ffde6f0 2022-07-23)`
